## Group Lead Route Templates

- Group task list route: `/api/v1/board-groups/{group_id}/tasks`
- Group task detail route: `/api/v1/board-groups/{group_id}/tasks/{task_id}`
- Group snapshot route: `/api/v1/board-groups/{group_id}/snapshot`
- Group chat route: `/api/v1/boards/{board_id}/group-memory`
- Board-scoped routes are for board leads, not group leads.

## Fast Query Helpers

- Group tasks:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/board-groups/$GROUP_ID/tasks?limit=50" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`
- Review tasks:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/board-groups/$GROUP_ID/tasks?status=review" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`
- Blocked tasks:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/board-groups/$GROUP_ID/tasks?status=blocked" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`
- Group snapshot:
  `curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/board-groups/$GROUP_ID/snapshot" -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`

## OpenAPI Refresh

```bash
mkdir -p api
curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/openapi.json" -o api/openapi.json
jq -r '
  .paths | to_entries[] as $p
  | $p.value | to_entries[]
  | select((.value.tags // []) | (index("agent-lead") or index("board-groups")))
  | "\(.key|ascii_upcase)\t\($p.key)\t\(.value.operationId // "-")\t\(.value[\"x-llm-intent\"] // "-")"
' api/openapi.json | sort > api/group-lead-operations.tsv
```

## API Discovery Policy

- Prefer operations whose path and tags match group-level work.
- Re-check OpenAPI before assuming payload shape or route availability.
- Do not use board-agent management routes for group-level work.
